Environmental Description: Evergreen monsoon-forests occur at springs and as narrow forests along more permanent creek lines. They are of limited occurrence on Cobourg. Dry monsoon forests are more common occurring along the coast and are often not associated with water sources or creek lines. Both types of monsoon forests have higher stem densities, greater basal area, more tree species, higher litter cover and lower grass cover than surrounding vegetation.

Source Description: Callitris intratropica open-forest/woodlands with mixed eucalyptus species.
Environmental Description: Found on ridge side slopes, dissected plateaux and on flat sand plains and is more prevalent in the south eastern portion of the park (the neck). Soils are generally sandy earths (tenosols to kandosols) of variable depth. Gravels to 35% occur in some regions. Red tenosols (earthy sands) occur with the cypress/eucalypt mix. Average slopes are 2%. Often found as clumps or patches within the Eucalyptus open-forests (mapunit 1). Scattered individuals also occur.

L5 Association: U ^Avicennia marina,Lumnitzera racemosa\^tree\6\r;G+ +/-^Halosarcia indica+/-Halosarcia halocnemoides+/-Suaeda arbusculoides\^chenopod shrub+/-tussock grass+/-sedge\1\r
Source Description: Low shrubland to low sparse chenopod shrubland of Halosarcia indica and Halosarcia halocnemoides.
Environmental Description: Includes bare salt flats and mudflats found on unconsolidated, generally hyper saline muds or muddy sands. Soils are supratidal hydrosols; salt crusted, black or grey cracking clay, inundated by salt water during spring tides (approx. bi-monthly or longer). There is some freshwater input during the wet season. These coastal flats are generally devoid of shrubs and trees, with a cover of succulents and grasses ranging from 0-80%. Although not contributing to the vegetation biomass they are significant areas in terms of primary productivity of the marine ecosystem. Patches of chenopod vegetation may occur within the broader salt-flat area.
Common Language Description: +/-Halosarcia indica, +/-Halosarcia halocnemoides, +/-Suaeda arbusculoides low sparse chenopod shrubland over Lumnitzera racemosa, Avicennia marina low open woodland
